<subSubSection box="[1006,1239,1113,1139]" pageId="9" pageNumber="79" type="vernacular_names">
<paragraph blockId="9.[895,1350,1079,1139]" box="[1006,1239,1113,1139]" pageId="9" pageNumber="79">Least horseshoe bat</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="79" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="9.[816,1429,1179,2019]" pageId="9" pageNumber="79">
This is a common bat species in 
<collectingCountry box="[1263,1337,1180,1206]" name="China" pageId="9" pageNumber="79">China</collectingCountry>
. 
<collectionCode box="[1352,1386,1180,1206]" pageId="9" pageNumber="79">FA</collectionCode>
— 
<quantity box="[816,998,1214,1240]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.795" metricValueMax="4.16" metricValueMin="3.4299999999999997" pageId="9" pageNumber="79" unit="mm" value="37.95" valueMax="41.6" valueMin="34.3">34.3–41.6 mm</quantity>
, mass — 
<quantity box="[1139,1259,1214,1240]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="kg" metricValue="5.55" metricValueMax="7.8" metricValueMin="3.3" pageId="9" pageNumber="79" unit="g" value="5.55" valueMax="7.8" valueMin="3.3">3.3–7.8 g</quantity>
, 
<collectionCode box="[1279,1382,1214,1240]" pageId="9" pageNumber="79">FMAXE</collectionCode>
— 100.3–111.2 kHz. Capture sites included 
<collectingRegion box="[1335,1424,1248,1274]" country="China" name="Beijing" pageId="9" pageNumber="79">Beijing</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[816,895,1282,1308]" country="China" name="Fujian" pageId="9" pageNumber="79">Fujian</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[918,1059,1282,1308]" country="China" name="Guangdong" pageId="9" pageNumber="79">Guangdong</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[1081,1186,1282,1308]" country="China" name="Guangxi" pageId="9" pageNumber="79">Guangxi</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[1209,1314,1282,1308]" country="China" name="Guizhou" pageId="9" pageNumber="79">Guizhou</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[1336,1424,1282,1308]" country="China" name="Hainan" pageId="9" pageNumber="79">Hainan</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[816,891,1316,1342]" country="China" name="Hubei" pageId="9" pageNumber="79">Hubei</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[912,1000,1316,1342]" country="China" name="Jiangxi" pageId="9" pageNumber="79">Jiangxi</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[1021,1141,1316,1342]" country="China" name="Shandong" pageId="9" pageNumber="79">Shandong</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[1162,1257,1316,1342]" country="China" name="Sichuan" pageId="9" pageNumber="79">Sichuan</collectingRegion>
and 
<collectingRegion box="[1332,1426,1316,1342]" country="China" name="Yunnan" pageId="9" pageNumber="79">Yunnan</collectingRegion>
. Among these sites, bats from 
<collectingRegion box="[1192,1278,1350,1376]" country="China" name="Beijing" pageId="9" pageNumber="79">Beijing</collectingRegion>
were larger than others (
<collectionCode box="[961,997,1383,1409]" pageId="9" pageNumber="79">FA</collectionCode>
<quantity box="[1004,1177,1383,1409]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.09" metricValueMax="4.16" metricValueMin="4.02" pageId="9" pageNumber="79" unit="mm" value="40.9" valueMax="41.6" valueMin="40.2">40.2–41.6 mm</quantity>
) and had a lower call frequency, ranging 105.2–109.7 kHz. For example, some 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Temminck" authorityYear="1834" box="[890,1019,1451,1477]" class="Mammalia" family="Rhinolophidae" genus="Rhinolophus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="79" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="pusillus">
<emphasis box="[890,1019,1451,1477]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="79">R. pusillus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingRegion box="[1100,1201,1451,1477]" country="China" name="Guangxi" pageId="9" pageNumber="79">Guangxi</collectingRegion>
called at a higher frequency (111.2 kHz) and are smaller (
<collectionCode box="[1390,1429,1485,1511]" pageId="9" pageNumber="79">FA</collectionCode>
<quantity box="[816,1005,1519,1545]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.655" metricValueMax="3.79" metricValueMin="3.52" pageId="9" pageNumber="79" unit="mm" value="36.55" valueMax="37.9" valueMin="35.2">35.2–37.9 mm</quantity>
). 
<bibRefCitation author="ROBINSON, M. F." box="[1036,1248,1519,1545]" pageId="9" pageNumber="79" pagination="389 - 393" refId="ref12136" refString="ROBINSON, M. F. 1996. A relationship between echolocation calls and noseleaf, widths in bats of the genera Rhinolophus and Hipposideros. Journal of Zoology (London), 239: 389 - 393." type="journal article" year="1996">Robinson (1996)</bibRefCitation>
reported that 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Temminck" authorityYear="1834" box="[816,943,1553,1579]" class="Mammalia" family="Rhinolophidae" genus="Rhinolophus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="79" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="pusillus">
<emphasis box="[816,943,1553,1579]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="79">R. pusillus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in 
<collectingCountry box="[988,1096,1553,1579]" name="Malaysia" pageId="9" pageNumber="79">Malaysia</collectingCountry>
calls at 92.5 kHz (
<collectionCode box="[1331,1367,1553,1579]" pageId="9" pageNumber="79">FA</collectionCode>
<quantity metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.8299999999999996" pageId="9" pageNumber="79" unit="mm" value="38.3">38.3 mm</quantity>
), and so it appears likely that cryptic species divisions are likely in this taxon across its range. 
<bibRefCitation author="LI, G. &amp; G. JONES &amp; S. J. ROSSITER &amp; S. - F. CHEN &amp; S. PARSONS &amp; S. ZHANG" pageId="9" pageNumber="79" pagination="1234 - 1240" refId="ref11837" refString="LI, G., G. JONES, S. J. ROSSITER, S. - F. CHEN, S. PARSONS, and S. ZHANG. 2006. Phylogenetics of small horseshoe bats from East Asia based on mitochondrial DNA sequence variation. Journal of Mammalogy, 87: 1234 - 1240." type="journal article" year="2006">
Li 
<emphasis box="[816,876,1654,1680]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="79">et al</emphasis>
. (2006)
</bibRefCitation>
suggested that bat taxa 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Temminck" authorityYear="1834" box="[1297,1428,1654,1680]" class="Mammalia" family="Rhinolophidae" genus="Rhinolophus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="79" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="pusillus">
<emphasis box="[1297,1428,1654,1680]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="79">R. pusillus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(sampled across 
<collectingCountry box="[1029,1104,1688,1714]" name="China" pageId="9" pageNumber="79">China</collectingCountry>
), 
<taxonomicName authorityName="K. Andersen" authorityYear="1905" box="[1132,1301,1688,1714]" class="Mammalia" family="Rhinolophidae" genus="Rhinolophus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="79" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="monoceros">
<emphasis box="[1132,1301,1688,1714]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="79">R. monoceros</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<collectingRegion box="[1324,1424,1688,1714]" country="China" name="Taiwan)" pageId="9" pageNumber="79">Taiwan)</collectingRegion>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[816,953,1722,1748]" class="Mammalia" family="Rhinolophidae" genus="Rhinolophus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="79" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="cornutus">
<emphasis box="[816,953,1722,1748]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="79">R. cornutus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(main islands of 
<collectingCountry box="[1161,1230,1722,1748]" name="Japan" pageId="9" pageNumber="79">Japan</collectingCountry>
) and 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="79">R. c. pumilus</emphasis>
(
<collectingRegion box="[869,980,1756,1782]" country="Japan" name="Okinawa" pageId="9" pageNumber="79">Okinawa</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[994,1063,1756,1782]" name="Japan" pageId="9" pageNumber="79">Japan</collectingCountry>
) are better considered as geographical subspecies rather than distinct species. 
<bibRefCitation author="SIMMONS, N. B." box="[816,1015,1823,1849]" pageId="9" pageNumber="79" refId="ref12299" refString="SIMMONS, N. B. 2005. Order Chiroptera. Pp. 312 - 525, in Mammal species of the World: a taxonomic and geographic reference, 3 rd edition (D. E. WILSON and D. M. REEDER, eds.). The Johns Hopkins University Press, Baltimore, 2142 pp." type="book" year="2005">Simmons (2005)</bibRefCitation>
considers that 
<taxonomicName box="[1200,1338,1823,1849]" class="Mammalia" family="Rhinolophidae" genus="Rhinolophus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="79" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="cornutus">
<emphasis box="[1200,1338,1823,1849]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="79">R. cornutus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is confined to 
<collectingCountry box="[920,987,1857,1883]" name="Japan" pageId="9" pageNumber="79">Japan</collectingCountry>
and, therefore, bats from 
<collectingCountry box="[1305,1375,1857,1883]" name="China" pageId="9" pageNumber="79">China</collectingCountry>
that were previously assigned to this taxon are now considered to belong to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Temminck" authorityYear="1834" box="[1059,1183,1925,1951]" class="Mammalia" family="Rhinolophidae" genus="Rhinolophus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="79" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="pusillus">
<emphasis box="[1059,1183,1925,1951]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="79">R. pusillus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
